  "transcript": {
    "language": "en",
    "is_generated": false,
    "segments": [
      {
        "start": 0.5,
        "duration": 1.2,
        "text": "- [David] Howdy, wordsmiths."
      },
      {
        "start": 1.7,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "I reckon it's just about\ntime for us to saddle up"
      },
      {
        "start": 4.2,
        "duration": 3.5,
        "text": "and get to knowledge town. Hyah!"
      },
      {
        "start": 7.7,
        "duration": 1.1,
        "text": "I've got three,"
      },
      {
        "start": 8.8,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "count 'em, three words to\ngo through with you today,"
      },
      {
        "start": 10.7,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "so let's get to it."
      },
      {
        "start": 12.8,
        "duration": 4.8,
        "text": "The words are simulate,\nleisure, and recreation."
      },
      {
        "start": 17.6,
        "duration": 1.3,
        "text": "I'll go through some definitions"
      },
      {
        "start": 18.9,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "and then we'll talk about\nsome of the word parts"
      },
      {
        "start": 20.9,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "that make up these words."
      },
      {
        "start": 22.7,
        "duration": 0.8,
        "text": "Simulate."
      },
      {
        "start": 23.6,
        "duration": 2.7,
        "text": "This is a verb that means to imitate,"
      },
      {
        "start": 26.3,
        "duration": 3.8,
        "text": "to create an imitation\nthat looks or feels real."
      },
      {
        "start": 30.1,
        "duration": 1.9,
        "text": "A simulation is a noun,"
      },
      {
        "start": 32.0,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "it's a virtual environment"
      },
      {
        "start": 33.4,
        "duration": 4.2,
        "text": "like on a computer, or an\nimitation of something, right?"
      },
      {
        "start": 37.6,
        "duration": 2.3,
        "text": "A flight simulator is a\npiece of computer software"
      },
      {
        "start": 40.0,
        "duration": 3.5,
        "text": "that lets you practice flying an airplane."
      },
      {
        "start": 43.5,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "This was the flight\nsimulator of my childhood,"
      },
      {
        "start": 46.0,
        "duration": 3.3,
        "text": "and lemme tell you, I was very bad at it."
      },
      {
        "start": 49.4,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "Do not let me fly a plane. I am not ready."
      },
      {
        "start": 52.0,
        "duration": 1.5,
        "text": "Leisure or leisure."
      },
      {
        "start": 53.5,
        "duration": 1.8,
        "text": "It's a noun. It means free time."
      },
      {
        "start": 55.2,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "It's what you do when\nyou're not at work or school"
      },
      {
        "start": 57.5,
        "duration": 1.7,
        "text": "and when you're not asleep."
      },
      {
        "start": 59.2,
        "duration": 1.1,
        "text": "About 200 years ago,"
      },
      {
        "start": 60.3,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "people with factory jobs\nworked horrible hours"
      },
      {
        "start": 63.3,
        "duration": 2.6,
        "text": "and fought for the eight-hour workday."
      },
      {
        "start": 66.0,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "Eight hours of work,\neight hours of leisure,"
      },
      {
        "start": 68.5,
        "duration": 1.7,
        "text": "eight hours of sleep."
      },
      {
        "start": 70.3,
        "duration": 0.8,
        "text": "That was their goal."
      },
      {
        "start": 71.1,
        "duration": 2.5,
        "text": "And what do you do during\nthose eight hours of leisure?"
      },
      {
        "start": 73.6,
        "duration": 1.4,
        "text": "Recreation."
      },
      {
        "start": 75.0,
        "duration": 3.0,
        "text": "A noun, it means\nentertainment and relaxation."
      },
      {
        "start": 78.0,
        "duration": 3.1,
        "text": "Things you do for fun,\nthings you do recreationally."
      },
      {
        "start": 81.2,
        "duration": 2.2,
        "text": "Hanging out with friends and family,"
      },
      {
        "start": 83.4,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "riding bikes, playing games,"
      },
      {
        "start": 85.4,
        "duration": 2.1,
        "text": "listening to music, going on adventures,"
      },
      {
